01:53:20,592 --> 01:53:22,373
Still no hands on Zoom, so we'll stay at the podium.

1156
01:53:22,473 --> 01:53:23,534
Name and address for the record, please.

1157
01:53:23,554 --> 01:53:24,134
You have three minutes.

1158
01:53:24,755 --> 01:53:25,035
OK.

1159
01:53:25,255 --> 01:53:28,117
Simon Elsindor, 44 Tainter Street, and?

1160
01:53:29,316 --> 01:53:48,245
The reason why I came up here is because my issue with this is not necessarily the overall fact that we're changing providers, but I think the issue that many people have pointed out is that there is a history of sketchy behavior when it comes to things like this from the mayor, of not only announcing things rather late and

1161
01:53:49,245 --> 01:54:03,731
in a way that catches everyone off guard, go back to the trashing, whatever, but also in a way that fundamentally changes the ways that we do things in Medford to a way that people clearly do not, that people clearly have issues with and want answers about.

1162
01:54:04,152 --> 01:54:11,735
There is no reason why we cannot get answers as to at least what the process was, even if we can't necessarily get things to change back.

1163
01:54:13,937 --> 01:54:17,959
What the public is requesting is just to know what this is about.

1164
01:54:18,599 --> 01:54:27,103
And it's very clear that there is some sort of story here that both sides are not currently going to tell for obvious reasons at this meeting.

1165
01:54:27,423 --> 01:54:29,024
But that is what this resolution is for.

1166
01:54:29,084 --> 01:54:32,846
This resolution is not saying we're changing this back or anything like that.

1167
01:54:33,126 --> 01:54:41,670
The resolution is stating that we are going to have hearing about this, we are going to have a review about what actually led to us getting into this situation in the first place.

1168
01:54:42,410 --> 01:54:49,014
I simply just do not see the reason why the city needs to be so defensive when it is clear that they did have a process.

1169
01:54:49,334 --> 01:54:57,819
If that process was indeed correct, then that should be something that we are able to talk about and actually have a normal conversation about at a separate meeting.

1170
01:54:58,979 --> 01:55:00,640
That is what puts me off about this most.

1171
01:55:00,660 --> 01:55:08,805
It's the fact that we as city officials getting disoffensive over the fact that, over the mere suggestion that there might have been something wrong.

1172
01:55:09,675 --> 01:55:27,278
That is personally just what concerns me the most, because personally, I wouldn't have thought anything of that before, but seeing how, seeing the responses of our city officials has only made me think that there may be something amiss.

1173
01:55:27,999 --> 01:55:30,859
There probably isn't, but I would like to know one way or the other.

1174
01:55:30,879 --> 01:55:33,960
Yeah, thank you.

1175
01:55:39,913 --> 01:55:41,414
Still no hands on Zoom, we'll stay at the podium.

1176
01:55:41,634 --> 01:55:42,615
Name and address for the record.

1177
01:55:42,635 --> 01:55:47,139
