1178
01:55:47,179 --> 01:55:49,020
I just want to make a general comment.

1179
01:55:49,661 --> 01:55:56,466
I think it's rather obvious that we have a problem with procurement contracts in this city.

1180
01:55:56,707 --> 01:55:58,388
I mean, this is a manifestation of it.

1181
01:55:58,908 --> 01:56:02,011
There's also manifestation on the municipal solid waste.

1182
01:56:02,251 --> 01:56:04,213
There's a lot of talking about what has happened.

1183
01:56:05,714 --> 01:56:10,878
I didn't know, for example, that this particular contract was exempt from Chapter 30B.

1184
01:56:11,598 --> 01:56:15,301
My understanding is that legal services are also exempt from Chapter 30B.

1185
01:56:17,302 --> 01:56:19,704
I believe now we lost our city solicitor again.

1186
01:56:21,426 --> 01:56:35,216
But even for municipal solid waste, which should be done according or was done according to Chapter 30B, I think we need to sort of revisit how procurement contracts are done.

1187
01:56:35,536 --> 01:56:38,979
And this is a body whose task is to legislate.

1188
01:56:39,719 --> 01:57:03,395
We it seems that we need to legislate in particular those things that are not subject to chapter 30 B So the city follows a competitive transparent open to the public bidding process Where we're not following sort of a reactive approach that you know, there's something happens to contract everyone finds out after the fact huge turmoil

1189
01:57:04,255 --> 01:57:07,617
And then we waste a bunch of time trying to fix it.

1190
01:57:08,758 --> 01:57:10,159
But rather we are proactive, right?

1191
01:57:10,179 --> 01:57:21,507
So the public, everyone, all the stakeholders, everyone that's involved is sort of like participants in the process before we actually make a decision.

1192
01:57:22,028 --> 01:57:26,531
So I just wanted to say that I think it's time to basically legislate this.

1193
01:57:26,671 --> 01:57:28,913
Again, in particular things that are exempt from Chapter 30B.

1194
01:57:29,713 --> 01:57:31,994
I think the city council should, you know, write something.

1195
01:57:32,594 --> 01:57:55,705
And so the mayor actually has to follow a competitive, transparent, open to the public bidding process where all the stakeholders, taxpayers, et cetera, we can be sort of part of the process as it happens in a proactive fashion rather than reactive after the fact when it's also very possibly limited what we can actually do.

1196
01:57:56,025 --> 01:57:56,505
Thank you so much.

1197
01:57:57,446 --> 01:57:57,706
Thank you.

1198
01:58:02,872 --> 01:58:12,075
Still no hands on Zoom, so we will let NBC 10 take their microphone, and then we will stay at the podium.

1199
01:58:12,715 --> 01:58:13,236
Sorry, Nick.

1200
01:58:13,736 --> 01:58:15,056
I'll live with it.

1201
01:58:15,516 --> 01:58:16,497
Name and address for the record.

1202
01:58:16,517 --> 01:58:17,197
You have three minutes.

1203
01:58:17,750 --> 01:58:19,131
Nick Giurleo, 40 Robinson Road.

1204
01:58:20,272 --> 01:58:27,938
I wasn't actually planning on speaking about this, believe it or not, but there was something that the mayor's chief of staff said that really stood out to me, really struck me.

1205
01:58:28,398 --> 01:58:34,623
She mentioned that carrying on this conversation would create, quote, concern and fear, unquote.

1206
01:58:35,384 --> 01:58:36,545
Carrying on the conversation.

1207
01:58:37,305 --> 01:58:41,529
In other words, simply talking about this will make residents worried.

1208
01:58:41,629 --> 01:58:43,950
Simply talking about this isn't in the public interest.

1209
01:58:44,071 --> 01:58:45,532
To me, that's just really, really,

1210
01:58:46,370 --> 01:58:49,011
shameful, a really kind of terrible thing to say.

1211
01:58:49,951 --> 01:58:57,133
This, what our city government does, you know, behind the scenes, behind closed doors, is something the public should know about.

1212
01:58:57,453 --> 01:59:01,334
We should know what's going on with these negotiations, with any negotiations.

1213
01:59:02,174 --> 01:59:10,557
I have tried to look for contracts that our city has entered into on the city website, and you would think, you know, you could just go onto the city website and it'd be an easy PDF download.

1214
01:59:10,577 --> 01:59:11,257
They're just not there.

1215
01:59:12,047 --> 01:59:17,732
And sometimes you reach out to department heads, you ask for contracts, and some of them are very cooperative and will give you the contract.

1216
01:59:17,832 --> 01:59:23,217
Others will dig their heels in, and you try to make a public records request, and there's heel digging in with that.

1217
01:59:23,937 --> 01:59:30,423
So many citizens, and just speaking on behalf of one who's not behind the podium here, just don't know what's going on in Medford.

1218
01:59:30,743 --> 01:59:32,305
You know, they just don't understand what our

1219
01:59:33,292 --> 01:59:34,273
city leadership is doing.

1220
01:59:34,293 --> 01:59:41,983
And, yes, to some extent, we vote for our leaders, we entrust them to make decisions for us to exercise leadership.

1221
01:59:42,003 --> 01:59:44,346
This is what the chief of police alluded to.

1222
01:59:44,726 --> 01:59:46,368
Yes, I understand and respect that.

1223
01:59:47,150 --> 01:59:53,954
But at the same time, the public does have a right to know what their elected leaders are doing so they can hold them accountable for the decisions they made.

1224
01:59:53,974 --> 01:59:59,538
If we don't know what our leaders are doing, we can't hold them accountable and make intelligent decisions come next election.

1225
01:59:59,958 --> 02:00:03,501
So this is very much in the public interest, and we really do need to flesh it out.

1226
02:00:03,601 --> 02:00:05,362
So I'm in full support of this resolution.

1227
02:00:05,442 --> 02:00:07,924
I think we need to keep this conversation going.

1228
02:00:08,304 --> 02:00:10,325
Armstrong has been with us for 25 years.

1229
02:00:10,826 --> 02:00:11,546
It's a long time.

1230
02:00:13,374 --> 02:00:15,775
By most accounts, they've been doing a good job at what they've been doing.

1231
02:00:15,956 --> 02:00:17,817
I know there's some dispute to the facts of that.

1232
02:00:18,377 --> 02:00:23,820
Let's investigate that, and let's get some more information on why there's belief in the administration that they're not doing a good job.

1233
02:00:24,461 --> 02:00:30,304
But I've only heard good things, and I don't understand why the mayor made this decision, and I'd like some answers.

1234
02:00:30,424 --> 02:00:31,665
And I think so many other people would.

1235
02:00:32,045 --> 02:00:35,187
And I hope our leaders will get those answers for the public.

1236
02:00:35,487 --> 02:00:35,787
Thank you.

1237
02:00:36,628 --> 02:00:36,888
Thank you.

