1241
02:00:45,527 --> 02:00:45,887
Good evening.

1242
02:00:46,427 --> 02:00:47,387
My name is Joe Musi.

1243
02:00:47,807 --> 02:00:49,187
I live on Bowen Ave in Medford.

1244
02:00:50,188 --> 02:00:51,088
I'm a Medford resident.

1245
02:00:51,568 --> 02:00:54,549
I work full time in consulting.

1246
02:00:55,069 --> 02:00:59,730
I own and manage several properties in the city of Medford, and I work 16 hours a week, roughly, for Armstrong.

1247
02:01:01,210 --> 02:01:04,451
So thank you for having us all, and I appreciate everyone that spoke before me.

1248
02:01:05,095 --> 02:01:09,757
So I made a decision to work for Armstrong how maybe several of my colleagues have.

1249
02:01:10,057 --> 02:01:19,702
I did a ride along with two companies and I chose Armstrong over the second company that I did a ride along with and they do serve neighboring communities.

1250
02:01:20,242 --> 02:01:29,726
So I found out about the news during Christmas break and I was interested to learn more as a resident of the city.

1251
02:01:30,027 --> 02:01:33,148
I'll speak from that lens not so much as an employee of Armstrong.

1252
02:01:34,120 --> 02:01:54,255
I work out of the Woburn base, so I'm not impacted by the decision necessarily, but I'm more concerned from the city standpoint, switching providers with this tight timeline of January 19th, how Cataldo plans to staff a base, provide 24-7 care to a city of Medford size.

1253
02:01:55,353 --> 02:02:01,975
I emailed the mayor several points requesting that information, and I did not receive a response, which was concerning.

1254
02:02:02,775 --> 02:02:13,637
And then I sent my resume to Cataldo, and two days before Christmas, they called me, and they are actively hiring full and part-time EMTs for the city.

1255
02:02:14,378 --> 02:02:20,199
Their first orientation class does not occur until the end of January, which is well after the deadline of the transition.

1256
02:02:20,879 --> 02:02:24,400
And the long-time employee has been there for over 20 years, said they have no plan.

1257
02:02:25,502 --> 02:02:28,965
for bases and they don't really know what they're doing yet for the rollout.

1258
02:02:29,485 --> 02:02:38,052
So naturally that is really alarming and I think everyone deserves to know that that is what was communicated from the staff to me at that point.

1259
02:02:39,253 --> 02:02:42,255
But again I just would like the city to have a plan.

1260
02:02:42,953 --> 02:02:44,054
and direct oversight.

1261
02:02:44,074 --> 02:02:51,340
I think there were some comments made earlier by some of our chiefs that said that we have to take their word, but we all know a private company can't govern itself.

1262
02:02:51,641 --> 02:02:59,668
There has to be oversight, and they have to be managed and held accountable, and simply just saying, oh, they told us this, we will trust them, is not going to work.

1263
02:03:00,088 --> 02:03:02,370
So I would like to see a plan of that transition.

1264
02:03:02,710 --> 02:03:10,036
It should be laid out very clearly, and it should state exactly what's being provided, how it's going to be staffed, and I think we need

1265
02:03:10,857 --> 02:03:15,861
something written down and shown to us where we can see and approve it, perhaps the timeline needs to be pushed slightly.

1266
02:03:16,221 --> 02:03:17,062
I think that's very reasonable.

1267
02:03:17,082 --> 02:03:17,882
There's no shame in that.

1268
02:03:18,343 --> 02:03:24,847
But I am concerned based on what I heard from Cataldo and what I didn't hear from the mayor is concerning.

1269
02:03:24,988 --> 02:03:25,288
Thank you.

1270
02:03:26,589 --> 02:03:26,909
Thank you.

